disconnectConduit:
Async: true

Disconnects the conduit at structure.

Parameters:
- `conduit` (MywFeature): Conduit to disconnect
- `housing` (MywFeature): Structure to disconnect conduit at
connectConduits:
Async: true

Connects two conduits at a structure.

Parameters:
- `housing` (MywFeature): Structure to connect the conduit to
- `first_conduit` (MywFeature): First conduit to connect
- `second_conduit` (Feature): Second conduit to connect
routeNestedConduits:
Async: true

Route new conduits for all conduits that are part of the conduit hierarchy.

Parameters:
- `conduitsJson` (Object): Serialized conduit hierarchy
- `structures` (Object): Serialized structures where conduits are being routed
- `parentConduits` (Object): Serialzied parent conduits in the hierarchy, used to set housing
- `transaction` (Transaction): Current update transaction, if not provided a new one will be created

Returns:
- (): conduits created in a single array
moveInto:
Async: true

Move conduit to a new housing in the same route

Parameters:
- `housing` (MywFeature): New conduit housing
- `feature` (MywFeature): Conduit to be moved
isContinuousConduitType:

- `feature` (MywFeature): Conduit to be checked

Returns:
